1
00:01:02,590 --> 00:01:05,252
From 1914 to 1918,

2
00:01:05,493 --> 00:01:08,292
World War I was waging in Europe.

3
00:01:08,529 --> 00:01:09,587
After the war ended

4
00:01:09,830 --> 00:01:11,457
the four great empires disintegrated.

5
00:01:11,699 --> 00:01:12,427
A trend of national consciousness

6
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:15,067
dominated the world.

7
00:01:19,206 --> 00:01:21,265
A quarter of a century has passed

8
00:01:21,509 --> 00:01:23,739
since Taiwan has lived
under Japan's colonial rule.

9
00:01:24,211 --> 00:01:25,576
It was the beginning of the

10
00:01:25,813 --> 00:01:28,282
Taisho Democracy in Japan.

11
00:01:28,616 --> 00:01:29,242
In Taiwan,

12
00:01:29,483 --> 00:01:32,316
an assimilation policy
was being carried out.

13
00:01:43,898 --> 00:01:44,763
There was a group of
young Taiwanese men

14
00:01:44,999 --> 00:01:47,661
born around 1895,

15
00:01:47,902 --> 00:01:49,495
who were studying in Japan
at the time.

16
00:01:50,037 --> 00:01:51,198
The exposure to a new

17
00:01:51,438 --> 00:01:53,338
culture and new thinking

18
00:01:53,574 --> 00:01:56,544
had aroused
their national consciousness.

19
00:02:12,192 --> 00:02:13,523
Meanwhile in China,

20
00:02:13,761 --> 00:02:16,662
the people overthrew
the Qing Empire.

21
00:02:20,634 --> 00:02:21,999
Eight years later

22
00:02:22,236 --> 00:02:24,500
came the influential
May Fourth Movement.

23
00:02:24,905 --> 00:02:27,203
An independence movement
also broke out in Korea.

24
00:02:27,808 --> 00:02:28,866
All these events further stimulated

25
00:02:29,109 --> 00:02:31,874
these young Taiwanese intellectuals.

26
00:02:55,936 --> 00:02:58,234
Law 63 treats the people of Taiwan

27
00:02:58,472 --> 00:03:00,406
as second class citizens.

28
00:03:02,943 --> 00:03:04,877
We've done everything
we could to abolish it

29
00:03:05,112 --> 00:03:06,807
without any success.

30
00:03:10,117 --> 00:03:11,175
We must think of a way

31
00:03:11,418 --> 00:03:13,079
to raise people's awareness about
this problem.

32
00:03:15,823 --> 00:03:17,484
The May Fourth Movement
in China

33
00:03:17,725 --> 00:03:18,817
and the March 1st Movement
in Korea

34
00:03:19,126 --> 00:03:20,685
are great inspiration for us.

35
00:03:24,932 --> 00:03:25,865
I think that we,

36
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:26,759
the Taiwanese people,

37
00:03:27,001 --> 00:03:28,298
should have our own organization.

38
00:03:28,535 --> 00:03:30,094
Only then can we have power, right?

39
00:03:30,337 --> 00:03:31,668
Mr. Lin...

40
00:03:31,939 --> 00:03:33,100
You're all here.

41
00:03:33,340 --> 00:03:34,273
Look...

42
00:03:34,508 --> 00:03:35,498
Today's newspaper.

43
00:03:42,516 --> 00:03:43,608
Listen.

44
00:03:44,852 --> 00:03:47,822
U.S. President Wilson has
announced his advocacy

45
00:03:48,088 --> 00:03:56,792
of self-determination
by ethnic groups.

46
00:03:58,465 --> 00:03:59,728
At the end of the 19th century,

47
00:03:59,967 --> 00:04:00,866
the Japanese society was influenced

48
00:04:01,101 --> 00:04:03,229
by thoughts in the world.

49
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:05,700
Ideas of freedom and
democracy began to spread.

50
00:04:05,939 --> 00:04:08,499
Socialism began to sprout.

51
00:04:10,144 --> 00:04:11,976
Around the time of World War I,

52
00:04:12,212 --> 00:04:14,180
the cry for national
self-determination was loud.

53
00:04:14,415 --> 00:04:15,610
More than 2000 Taiwanese students

54
00:04:15,849 --> 00:04:17,977
studying in Japan at the time

55
00:04:18,218 --> 00:04:20,277
were impacted by these thoughts

56
00:04:20,521 --> 00:04:23,752
and began to take notice of
political issues at home.

57
00:04:24,858 --> 00:04:28,385
This is a chance for
national self-determination.

58
00:04:28,629 --> 00:04:32,930
The independence and
full sovereignties of

59
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:38,037
all Balkan countries are guaranteed.

60
00:04:40,074 --> 00:04:40,939
Look here.

61
00:04:41,175 --> 00:04:42,665
Ireland and Korea

62
00:04:42,910 --> 00:04:44,844
these colonies intend to
become independent

63
00:04:45,079 --> 00:04:46,569
and to break away from
the colonial rule.

64
00:04:46,814 --> 00:04:48,339
Why can Korea

65
00:04:48,582 --> 00:04:49,344
become an independent country

66
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:50,675
and we can't?

67
00:04:50,918 --> 00:04:52,943
Yeah...

68
00:04:54,588 --> 00:04:56,113
From the looks of things,

69
00:04:56,356 --> 00:04:57,289
I feel that global trends

70
00:04:57,524 --> 00:04:58,582
are working in our favor.

71
00:04:58,826 --> 00:04:59,657
As long as we work hard

72
00:04:59,893 --> 00:05:00,257
and stick together,

73
00:05:00,494 --> 00:05:01,052
we can do it, too.

74
00:05:01,295 --> 00:05:03,093
Yes...

75
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:04,320
Mr. Lin is right.

76
00:05:04,565 --> 00:05:06,659
We must follow global trends.

77
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,561
Taiwanese people must not
be the second class citizens.

78
00:05:08,802 --> 00:05:09,792
Right...

79
00:05:10,104 --> 00:05:11,196
So how we must discuss

80
00:05:11,438 --> 00:05:12,234
what methods we are going to use

81
00:05:12,473 --> 00:05:13,736
to address our rights

82
00:05:13,974 --> 00:05:15,874
to the Taiwanese government.

83
00:05:16,910 --> 00:05:19,880
In 1919,
Korea's independence movement

84
00:05:20,114 --> 00:05:21,707
shocked the Japanese government
and its people.

85
00:05:21,949 --> 00:05:23,644
After Prime Minister Hara
took office,

86
00:05:23,884 --> 00:05:26,148
he proposed an assimilation policy

87
00:05:26,487 --> 00:05:29,548
to treat colonies
as extensions of Japan

88
00:05:29,790 --> 00:05:31,849
and to assimilate
the people of these lands

89
00:05:32,126 --> 00:05:34,060
into the Japanese culture.

90
00:05:34,461 --> 00:05:36,190
We should focus on this point

91
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:38,296
in our fight for
the rights of our people.

92
00:05:39,466 --> 00:05:40,228
Mr. Tsai.

93
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:40,831
Mr. Lin.

94
00:05:41,068 --> 00:05:41,796
You're all here.

95
00:05:42,136 --> 00:05:45,037
In 1920, a group of
Taiwanese students

96
00:05:45,272 --> 00:05:46,865
in Tokyo founded
the New People Association.

97
00:05:47,241 --> 00:05:49,039
They wanted to find a way

98
00:05:49,276 --> 00:05:51,176
to release Taiwanese people

99
00:05:51,411 --> 00:05:52,606
from political injustice.

100
00:05:54,081 --> 00:05:56,049
Its founding is credited to

101
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:58,947
the dedication and hard work

102
00:05:59,219 --> 00:06:00,778
of Lin Hsien-Tang and Tsai Hui-Ju,

103
00:06:01,088 --> 00:06:03,056
who frequently traveled to
Tokyo for the cause.

104
00:06:09,863 --> 00:06:12,161
I oppose treating Taiwan
as an extension of Japan.

105
00:06:12,399 --> 00:06:13,264
Needless to say,

106
00:06:13,534 --> 00:06:14,433
it is just

107
00:06:14,668 --> 00:06:16,796
an assimilation policy.

108
00:06:17,104 --> 00:06:17,969
It's simple.

109
00:06:18,205 --> 00:06:19,400
They want to turn us

110
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:20,903
into one of them.

111
00:06:21,241 --> 00:06:22,072
That's right.

112
00:06:22,242 --> 00:06:22,800
So we advocate treating

113
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:24,669
Taiwan as an unique entity.

114
00:06:24,912 --> 00:06:26,880
We must ask
the Japanese government

115
00:06:27,114 --> 00:06:28,946
to establish a parliament in Taiwan

116
00:06:29,183 --> 00:06:31,277
to make laws and to review budget.

117
00:06:32,219 --> 00:06:33,084
Yes.

118
00:06:33,253 --> 00:06:34,084
Very good.

119
00:06:34,488 --> 00:06:35,717
In 1920,

120
00:06:35,956 --> 00:06:38,789
these men published
The Taiwan Youth

121
00:06:39,059 --> 00:06:40,857
to publicize their ideas
of reformation

122
00:06:41,261 --> 00:06:43,355
while carrying out
a 14-year long petition

123
00:06:43,597 --> 00:06:46,123
for the establishment of
a parliament in Taiwan

124
00:06:46,366 --> 00:06:48,095
to fight for the right to self-rule.

125
00:06:52,773 --> 00:06:55,799
They elected Lin Hsien-Tang
as their first chairman.

126
00:06:56,076 --> 00:06:57,635
They also returned to Taiwan
on their holidays.

127
00:06:57,878 --> 00:06:59,812
They went to different places
in Taiwan

128
00:07:00,113 --> 00:07:01,376
to persuade people to support them.

129
00:07:01,615 --> 00:07:03,640
Please support the idea of
setting up a parliament.

130
00:07:04,251 --> 00:07:06,583
Please support the idea of
setting up a parliament.

131
00:07:06,987 --> 00:07:07,749
Please.

132
00:07:07,988 --> 00:07:10,218
Please support the idea of
setting up a parliament.

133
00:07:11,425 --> 00:07:12,085
Go! Go!

134
00:07:12,326 --> 00:07:13,487
Sign here.

135
00:07:14,494 --> 00:07:16,792
Please support the idea of
setting up a parliament.

136
00:07:17,197 --> 00:07:18,187
Please.

137
00:07:24,838 --> 00:07:26,067
The Governor-General to Taiwan

138
00:07:27,107 --> 00:07:31,374
holds legislative power
in his left hand

139
00:07:31,612 --> 00:07:34,138
and administrative power in his right.

140
00:07:35,449 --> 00:07:38,043
His actions violate the
Constitution of the Japanese Empire.

141
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:42,289
Aren't Taiwanese human beings?

142
00:07:42,823 --> 00:07:45,554
Why aren't we protected
by the Constitution?

143
00:07:46,793 --> 00:07:48,192
Legislative power should be

144
00:07:48,428 --> 00:07:50,021
returned to the Taiwanese.

145
00:07:50,464 --> 00:07:51,329
Am I right?

146
00:07:51,565 --> 00:07:53,226
You are right.

147
00:07:57,170 --> 00:08:00,731
So we demand the setting up
of a parliament.

148
00:08:01,408 --> 00:08:04,036
The situation in Taiwan is
different from that in Japan.

149
00:08:04,244 --> 00:08:05,712
It needs separate legislation

150
00:08:05,946 --> 00:08:06,936
and the people of Taiwan

151
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:08,705
should be able to review
its own budget.

152
00:08:08,949 --> 00:08:10,781
Right.

153
00:08:17,391 --> 00:08:20,088
For 14 years since 1921,

154
00:08:20,327 --> 00:08:22,386
15 such petitions

155
00:08:22,629 --> 00:08:24,393
were organized.

156
00:08:24,698 --> 00:08:27,065
Even though no concrete results
were achieved,

157
00:08:27,301 --> 00:08:29,702
the petitioners received
great publicity

158
00:08:29,937 --> 00:08:32,463
on their visits to Japan.

159
00:08:34,508 --> 00:08:36,772
Each time when returning
to Taiwan,

160
00:08:37,044 --> 00:08:37,909
they were supported

161
00:08:38,145 --> 00:08:40,705
strongly by people.

162
00:08:41,381 --> 00:08:43,042
This continuous action

163
00:08:43,283 --> 00:08:45,581
deeply affected
the Japanese government.

164
00:08:45,819 --> 00:08:47,184
Finally, at the end of 1923,
the prosecution of violators

165
00:08:47,421 --> 00:08:49,253
of the Public Order and
Police Law took place.

166
00:08:49,523 --> 00:08:51,821
The Office of
Taiwan Governor-General

167
00:08:52,059 --> 00:08:53,823
conducted a large-scale
arrest of these activists.

168
00:09:25,759 --> 00:09:27,386
This was how Tsai Pei-Huo

169
00:09:27,627 --> 00:09:29,152
described this incident.

170
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:35,530
On the morning of
December 16, 1923,

171
00:09:36,036 --> 00:09:37,060
policemen all over Taiwan

172
00:09:37,304 --> 00:09:39,636
searched the houses

173
00:09:39,873 --> 00:09:42,467
of key petitioners.

174
00:09:43,043 --> 00:09:44,533
Some were arrested

175
00:09:45,078 --> 00:09:46,876
and over 60 people were
reported to the authorities.

176
00:09:47,114 --> 00:09:49,139
It shocked the people of Taiwan.

177
00:09:50,317 --> 00:09:51,079
This incident had great impact

178
00:09:51,318 --> 00:09:53,810
on the imperial government.

179
00:09:54,054 --> 00:09:56,455
So the administration officials
in Taiwan

180
00:09:56,523 --> 00:09:57,456
didn't dare do what they wanted to

181
00:09:57,858 --> 00:10:00,350
do but reduce the number
of the accused.

182
00:10:01,328 --> 00:10:05,629
Chiang Wei-Shui and I
were imprisoned for 4 months,

183
00:10:05,866 --> 00:10:07,300
which was the severest sentence.

184
00:10:08,468 --> 00:10:09,230
But these people

185
00:10:09,469 --> 00:10:11,494
were not defeated.

186
00:10:11,772 --> 00:10:13,900
On the contrary,
their morale was raised.

187
00:10:14,341 --> 00:10:14,807
After their release,

188
00:10:15,075 --> 00:10:17,806
they continued the petition.

189
00:10:21,782 --> 00:10:24,046
The island of Formosa is beautiful.

190
00:10:24,251 --> 00:10:25,912
Our ancestors settled down here.

191
00:10:26,153 --> 00:10:28,383
We cultivate the land
and plant the trees.

192
00:10:28,622 --> 00:10:30,647
We work hard from
one generation to the next.

193
00:10:30,891 --> 00:10:33,053
You must understand.
You must understand.

194
00:10:33,226 --> 00:10:34,751
We are pioneers.

195
00:10:35,028 --> 00:10:36,689
We are not ignorant slaves.

196
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:39,260
Hurry, Taiwan, to rule yourself.

197
00:10:39,499 --> 00:10:41,627
We have the right to
manage the public affairs.

198
00:10:45,472 --> 00:10:47,907
While the Petition for

199
00:10:48,141 --> 00:10:48,903
the Establishment of
a Taiwan Parliament

200
00:10:49,142 --> 00:10:51,236
was taking place
throughout the island,

201
00:10:51,611 --> 00:10:54,012
Chiang Wei-Shui,
a doctor at Tataocheng,

202
00:10:54,214 --> 00:10:56,182
made a diagnosis of Taiwan.

203
00:10:57,117 --> 00:10:59,051
On first consultation,

204
00:10:59,286 --> 00:11:02,017
the patient is found
to have a large skull,

205
00:11:02,589 --> 00:11:05,923
which would signify that
he is a thinking person.

206
00:11:06,827 --> 00:11:10,058
But a test of common sense proved

207
00:11:10,297 --> 00:11:13,198
his answers are irrelevant.

208
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:17,035
It is evident the patient
is feebleminded.

209
00:11:17,437 --> 00:11:19,030
Even though he has a large skull,

210
00:11:19,206 --> 00:11:21,334
he does not have any ideas.

211
00:11:23,376 --> 00:11:26,073
Chiang Wei-Shui wrote
a prescription for Taiwan.

212
00:11:26,313 --> 00:11:27,940
He believed the viable solution

213
00:11:28,181 --> 00:11:30,309
lied in cultural movements.

214
00:11:31,318 --> 00:11:32,808
In October of 1921,

215
00:11:33,086 --> 00:11:35,555
with the support of Lin Hsien-Tang,

216
00:11:35,789 --> 00:11:37,154
Chiang Wei-Shui founded
Taiwan Culture Association

217
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:39,552
at Blessed Imelda Girls High School.

218
00:11:41,761 --> 00:11:43,820
What the Taiwanese suffer from

219
00:11:44,397 --> 00:11:47,196
is a severe case of
information deficiency

220
00:11:48,635 --> 00:11:51,627
It can only be cured by

221
00:11:52,239 --> 00:11:55,334
a large dose of
knowledge supplements.

222
00:11:56,943 --> 00:11:58,411
And cultural movement is

223
00:11:58,645 --> 00:12:02,445
a treatment for the cause
of this symptom.

224
00:12:02,949 --> 00:12:06,078
Taiwan Culture Association
is an institution

225
00:12:06,319 --> 00:12:09,220
that conducts research and
provides causal treatments.

226
00:12:10,123 --> 00:12:12,057
For the sake of the future
of the Taiwanese

227
00:12:12,492 --> 00:12:15,018
please continue to support
Taiwan Culture Association

228
00:12:15,395 --> 00:12:16,419
Thank you.

229
00:12:22,569 --> 00:12:24,367
With the help of
Taiwan Culture Association

230
00:12:24,604 --> 00:12:26,402
men with insight on the island

231
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,267
began to form a network.

232
00:12:28,675 --> 00:12:31,042
With ideals and passions,

233
00:12:31,278 --> 00:12:33,007
in cities and countryside

234
00:12:33,246 --> 00:12:34,304
from north to south

235
00:12:34,548 --> 00:12:35,709
from west to east,

236
00:12:35,949 --> 00:12:37,348
they delivered speeches
on cultural issues,

237
00:12:37,584 --> 00:12:38,574
gave newspaper readings,

238
00:12:38,818 --> 00:12:39,546
produced cultural dramas,

239
00:12:39,786 --> 00:12:40,685
showed movies,

240
00:12:40,921 --> 00:12:42,787
and offered summer programs.

241
00:12:43,089 --> 00:12:44,420
They launched the
enlightenment movement

242
00:12:44,658 --> 00:12:46,626
of contemporary Taiwan culture.

243
00:12:58,104 --> 00:13:01,836
Our actions may be controlled.

244
00:13:03,310 --> 00:13:07,770
Our speeches may also be controlled.

245
00:13:09,316 --> 00:13:11,683
What is happiness

246
00:13:13,353 --> 00:13:16,084
to the people who are being ruled?

247
00:13:16,957 --> 00:13:19,927
The most important thing
is to set one's heart free.

248
00:13:20,727 --> 00:13:23,822
If one's heart is not free

249
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:25,723
and one is constrained...

250
00:13:25,999 --> 00:13:27,125
Besides lectures

251
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:28,664
and newspaper readings,

252
00:13:28,902 --> 00:13:31,462
Taiwan Culture Association
also utilize two powerful

253
00:13:31,705 --> 00:13:34,504
media: dramas and movies.

254
00:13:35,075 --> 00:13:36,167
In 1926,

255
00:13:36,409 --> 00:13:39,106
Taiwan Culture Association
organized a team called

256
00:13:39,346 --> 00:13:41,144
Beautiful Taiwan to show movies.

257
00:13:41,381 --> 00:13:42,109
It toured the island showing movies

258
00:13:42,349 --> 00:13:44,647
to educate the public.

259
00:13:44,884 --> 00:13:47,376
At the same time,
it delivered speeches and

260
00:13:47,621 --> 00:13:50,249
commented on political issues.

261
00:13:50,590 --> 00:13:52,115
We have beautiful villages,

262
00:13:52,359 --> 00:13:56,227
vast sea and high mountains.

263
00:13:56,463 --> 00:13:58,090
Please take this seriously.

264
00:13:58,331 --> 00:14:03,132
Then we will have a happy life.

265
00:14:04,704 --> 00:14:05,535
Look.

266
00:14:05,772 --> 00:14:08,469
A deer is walking in the forest.

267
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:11,503
It's not just taking a walk,

268
00:14:11,745 --> 00:14:13,304
but searching for food.

269
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:14,613
Look.

270
00:14:14,848 --> 00:14:16,646
Even a deer

271
00:14:17,117 --> 00:14:18,175
must fill its stomach

272
00:14:18,418 --> 00:14:19,579
to sustain itself.

273
00:14:19,819 --> 00:14:21,583
Getting fed is the basic
requirement for one's life

274
00:14:21,955 --> 00:14:23,320
Look.

275
00:14:23,556 --> 00:14:25,923
The people of Taiwan

276
00:14:26,159 --> 00:14:27,888
under Japanese rule

277
00:14:28,128 --> 00:14:30,426
are suffering more and more.

278
00:14:30,664 --> 00:14:31,563
The narrator paused.

279
00:14:31,798 --> 00:14:32,560
Today...

280
00:14:32,799 --> 00:14:35,166
Today a deer is going to

281
00:14:35,435 --> 00:14:37,597
drink water by the creek.

282
00:14:37,837 --> 00:14:42,070
The view is more beautiful than ever.

283
00:14:42,442 --> 00:14:43,068
One deer.

284
00:14:43,310 --> 00:14:44,402
Two deers.

285
00:14:44,644 --> 00:14:45,907
Three deers.

286
00:14:46,146 --> 00:14:48,478
Everyone is happy.

287
00:14:49,649 --> 00:14:50,844
In 1927,

288
00:14:51,084 --> 00:14:52,552
People's Newspaper of Taiwan,

289
00:14:52,786 --> 00:14:54,481
published by Taiwanese students
in Tokyo,

290
00:14:54,721 --> 00:14:56,917
was finally permitted to circulate
in Taiwan.

291
00:14:57,290 --> 00:14:59,816
The Taiwan Youth has changed
into Taiwan,

292
00:15:00,126 --> 00:15:02,356
and then into
People's Newspaper of Taiwan.

293
00:15:02,595 --> 00:15:04,393
This newspaper mainly
explored cultural,

294
00:15:04,631 --> 00:15:07,726
economic, political,
and social problems in Taiwan.

295
00:15:08,101 --> 00:15:10,468
It also criticized the Japanese rule

296
00:15:10,704 --> 00:15:13,605
and introduced situations
and thoughts in the world.

297
00:15:14,874 --> 00:15:18,071
People's Newspaper of Taiwan
worked together with

298
00:15:18,244 --> 00:15:20,679
Taiwan Culture Association.

299
00:15:20,914 --> 00:15:23,884
They started an era of cultural
enlightenment and cultural awakening.

300
00:15:42,135 --> 00:15:44,035
With the success of
Russian Revolution of 1917,

301
00:15:44,204 --> 00:15:45,069
in the 1920s

302
00:15:45,305 --> 00:15:48,172
socialism became the mainstream.

303
00:15:48,441 --> 00:15:50,466
More and more young leftists

304
00:15:50,710 --> 00:15:52,906
joined Taiwan Culture Association.

305
00:15:53,246 --> 00:15:55,613
The conflict between
the left and the right

306
00:15:55,849 --> 00:15:57,874
finally reached the climax.

307
00:15:58,118 --> 00:15:59,051
But the interests of

308
00:15:59,219 --> 00:16:00,948
proletarian farmers and laborers

309
00:16:01,187 --> 00:16:04,452
are different from
those of small landholders.

310
00:16:04,791 --> 00:16:05,781
The problem is that class struggle

311
00:16:06,092 --> 00:16:09,551
does not lead to social evolution.

312
00:16:09,963 --> 00:16:12,057
It is merely a disease

313
00:16:12,298 --> 00:16:14,062
caused by social evolution.

314
00:16:14,367 --> 00:16:15,391
Yeah.

315
00:16:15,969 --> 00:16:17,903
We have high ideals,

316
00:16:18,304 --> 00:16:21,899
but we still have to face the reality.

317
00:16:22,175 --> 00:16:24,075
That's compromising.

318
00:16:32,819 --> 00:16:33,581
Mr. Lin.

319
00:16:34,020 --> 00:16:36,045
Sorry. I have to run.

320
00:16:36,289 --> 00:16:37,586
In January of 1927,

321
00:16:37,824 --> 00:16:39,792
Taiwan Culture Association split up.

322
00:16:40,059 --> 00:16:42,084
The left force headed by

323
00:16:42,328 --> 00:16:43,261
Lian Wen-Ching and
Wang Min-Chuang

324
00:16:43,496 --> 00:16:45,464
took control of the association.

325
00:16:45,698 --> 00:16:48,030
Old members such as
Lin Hsien-Tang

326
00:16:48,268 --> 00:16:50,032
and Chiang Wei-Shui withdrew

327
00:16:50,270 --> 00:16:52,068
and founded Taiwan People's Party.

328
00:16:52,539 --> 00:16:55,509
It was Taiwan's first political party.

329
00:16:55,942 --> 00:16:59,037
It advocated protecting
the rights of the Taiwanese.

330
00:16:59,646 --> 00:17:01,580
The New Taiwan Culture Association

331
00:17:01,815 --> 00:17:03,840
led farm worker's movements.

332
00:17:04,083 --> 00:17:05,676
It directed the leftist movement

333
00:17:05,919 --> 00:17:07,887
in the late 1920s.

334
00:17:10,490 --> 00:17:12,049
The development of capitalism
in Japan

335
00:17:12,258 --> 00:17:15,057
has been the same as that
in Europe and America.

336
00:17:15,628 --> 00:17:18,120
The Japanese will surely squeeze

337
00:17:18,364 --> 00:17:19,729
as much as they can

338
00:17:19,966 --> 00:17:23,061
out of their colonies.

339
00:17:23,369 --> 00:17:24,859
Taiwanese people,

340
00:17:25,138 --> 00:17:26,128
Wake up.

341
00:17:26,973 --> 00:17:27,872
And fight.

342
00:17:28,107 --> 00:17:29,131
The narrator pauses.

343
00:17:29,375 --> 00:17:30,638
The people of Taiwan,

344
00:17:30,877 --> 00:17:31,867
look, the battlefield is near.

345
00:17:32,111 --> 00:17:33,408
Listen, the trumpet sounds calling
for marching.

346
00:17:33,646 --> 00:17:34,477
Stop!

347
00:17:34,714 --> 00:17:35,545
Advance!

348
00:17:35,782 --> 00:17:36,544
Advance!

349
00:17:36,783 --> 00:17:37,909
Advance!

350
00:17:38,151 --> 00:17:39,676
Advance!

351
00:17:39,919 --> 00:17:41,011
Stop!

352
00:17:41,955 --> 00:17:42,854
The narrator pauses.

353
00:17:43,089 --> 00:17:44,579
Advance!

354
00:17:44,824 --> 00:17:46,019
Advance!

355
00:17:46,192 --> 00:17:47,751
After World War I,

356
00:17:48,061 --> 00:17:49,620
Japan carried out the
economic policy of developing

357
00:17:49,863 --> 00:17:51,854
an industrial Japan
and an agricultural Taiwan.

358
00:17:52,465 --> 00:17:55,093
The produce of rice and
sugarcane soared

359
00:17:55,535 --> 00:17:57,560
but Taiwanese farmers
couldn't share

360
00:17:57,804 --> 00:18:00,136
gains of the economic growth.

361
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:01,835
Most of the profits were taken away

362
00:18:02,075 --> 00:18:04,510
by landholders and capitalists.

363
00:18:09,516 --> 00:18:10,779
This is terrible.

364
00:18:11,084 --> 00:18:11,778
What did they say?

365
00:18:12,085 --> 00:18:13,917
They said if some sugarcane
did not grow well,

366
00:18:14,153 --> 00:18:15,245
the sugar factory would deduct
the amount of the sugarcane.

367
00:18:15,488 --> 00:18:17,388
The factory decided
how much they deduct.

368
00:18:17,624 --> 00:18:19,649
There is something wrong
with their scale.

369
00:18:19,893 --> 00:18:20,655
The amount of the sugarcane
measured by them

370
00:18:20,894 --> 00:18:23,363
is half of the amount measured by us.

371
00:18:23,596 --> 00:18:24,859
Every one says sugarcane
growers who bring their

372
00:18:25,098 --> 00:18:26,930
sugarcane to be measured by
the sugar association are fools.

373
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:28,133
How can this happen?

374
00:18:28,368 --> 00:18:29,767
Can they really do this?

375
00:18:30,003 --> 00:18:30,299
That's right.

376
00:18:30,537 --> 00:18:33,370
Then our hard work for the
whole year is wasted.

377
00:18:33,773 --> 00:18:35,298
I get depressed
whenever I think about that.

378
00:18:37,043 --> 00:18:38,340
Yeah.

379
00:18:38,578 --> 00:18:40,046
We can't live like this.

380
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:42,314
In October of 1925,

381
00:18:42,549 --> 00:18:44,313
the sugarcane farmers
in Erlin, Changhua area

382
00:18:44,551 --> 00:18:47,020
stood up to the sugar factory

383
00:18:47,253 --> 00:18:49,051
and collided
with the Japanese police.

384
00:18:53,059 --> 00:18:54,584
On October 22,
more than 30 people from

385
00:18:55,595 --> 00:18:58,724
the sugar association
and 7 Japanese policemen

386
00:18:58,965 --> 00:19:02,026
took some laborers to cut sugarcane.

387
00:19:02,368 --> 00:19:04,097
We had more than 100

388
00:19:04,337 --> 00:19:06,305
sugarcane farmers on our side.

389
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:08,305
The farmers group

390
00:19:08,541 --> 00:19:10,202
told us to stop them,

391
00:19:10,443 --> 00:19:11,842
but they were insistent on
cutting sugarcane.

392
00:19:12,745 --> 00:19:14,907
So a collision broke out.

393
00:19:15,582 --> 00:19:18,483
The knives of two policemen

394
00:19:18,718 --> 00:19:20,277
were taken by the farmers.

395
00:19:20,853 --> 00:19:24,551
The police came the next day.

396
00:19:25,391 --> 00:19:29,487
93 people were arrested.

397
00:19:30,697 --> 00:19:33,064
They were like bandits.

398
00:19:34,667 --> 00:19:36,066
Bandits.

399
00:19:45,411 --> 00:19:46,606
The following year
after Erlin Incident,

400
00:19:46,846 --> 00:19:49,247
Association of Taiwanese
Farmers, a movement group of

401
00:19:49,482 --> 00:19:51,507
farmers in Taiwan, was established.

402
00:20:03,696 --> 00:20:06,290
It's a beautiful day.

403
00:20:06,733 --> 00:20:08,633
What are they doing?

404
00:20:10,903 --> 00:20:11,768
Just ignore them.

405
00:20:12,071 --> 00:20:14,335
It's nothing significant.

406
00:20:14,574 --> 00:20:15,268
Yeah.

407
00:20:15,508 --> 00:20:16,441
Cheers. Cheers.

408
00:20:17,343 --> 00:20:19,539
1928 was a prosperous year

409
00:20:19,779 --> 00:20:21,338
for labor movements in Taiwan.

410
00:20:21,881 --> 00:20:24,782
Guided by Chiang of
Taiwan People's Party,

411
00:20:25,084 --> 00:20:28,076
labor unions across the island
got together

412
00:20:28,321 --> 00:20:30,722
and formed Taiwan Laborers Union.

413
00:20:31,224 --> 00:20:32,123
In the meantime,

414
00:20:32,358 --> 00:20:34,190
Taiwan Communist Party
founded in

415
00:20:34,427 --> 00:20:35,553
Shanghai's French Concession

416
00:20:35,795 --> 00:20:37,559
returned to Taiwan
to do their activities.

417
00:20:37,797 --> 00:20:40,232
They presented the ideas
of Taiwanese as a hew people

418
00:20:40,466 --> 00:20:42,992
and Taiwan as an
independent country.

419
00:20:47,173 --> 00:20:48,538
In 1930,

420
00:20:48,775 --> 00:20:50,504
Yang Chao-Chia
went further to form

421
00:20:50,743 --> 00:20:52,643
Taiwanese Union of
Local Self-Government

422
00:20:52,879 --> 00:20:55,041
and requested that
the Taiwanese should

423
00:20:55,281 --> 00:20:56,214
have the right to vote.

424
00:20:59,852 --> 00:21:01,251
At the end of 1935,

425
00:21:01,487 --> 00:21:02,420
Taiwan finally had

426
00:21:02,655 --> 00:21:05,056
its first election for
local self-government.

427
00:21:20,540 --> 00:21:23,510
In order to have a fair election,

428
00:21:24,077 --> 00:21:25,169
several months before the election,

429
00:21:25,411 --> 00:21:26,105
we mobilized all of

430
00:21:26,345 --> 00:21:28,780
cadre members of the Union

431
00:21:29,082 --> 00:21:33,349
to cities and countryside

432
00:21:33,653 --> 00:21:36,486
to instill ideas of justice
into people

433
00:21:36,723 --> 00:21:38,782
so that they know how to cast ballots.

434
00:21:42,628 --> 00:21:44,619
But this first-ever election

435
00:21:44,864 --> 00:21:46,628
in Taiwan was full of flaws

436
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:47,931
because the Japanese
government only allowed

437
00:21:48,167 --> 00:21:50,033
half of the government
officials to be elected and

438
00:21:50,269 --> 00:21:52,533
the other half still to be
nominated by the government.

439
00:21:53,106 --> 00:21:55,973
Besides, the voter must be
male not younger than 25

440
00:21:56,209 --> 00:21:58,234
years of age and he should

441
00:21:58,478 --> 00:21:59,968
pay tax over 5 yuan annually.

442
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:01,613
During this period,

443
00:22:01,848 --> 00:22:02,872
Chiang Wei-Shui,
one of the important leaders of

444
00:22:03,116 --> 00:22:05,642
political and social
movements in modern Taiwan,

445
00:22:05,885 --> 00:22:07,546
passed away.

446
00:22:07,854 --> 00:22:09,788
In August of 1931,

447
00:22:10,656 --> 00:22:13,353
6 months after the ban
on Taiwan People's Party,

448
00:22:14,927 --> 00:22:18,522
Mr. Chiang succumbed to a cold.

449
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:22,162
Before his passing,

450
00:22:23,169 --> 00:22:26,571
I traveled up from Tainan to see him.

451
00:22:28,107 --> 00:22:33,841
We shook hands and cried.

452
00:22:38,084 --> 00:22:40,416
He said in a feeble voice,

453
00:22:41,187 --> 00:22:42,313
"Brother Pei-Huo,

454
00:22:43,089 --> 00:22:45,490
take care and best of luck.”

455
00:22:47,527 --> 00:22:50,292
I said, "Brother Chiang,

456
00:22:50,696 --> 00:22:52,425
go in peace.

457
00:22:53,599 --> 00:22:55,067
I will carry on

458
00:22:55,368 --> 00:22:57,132
the work for our people.

459
00:22:58,104 --> 00:22:59,902
Please do not worry."

460
00:23:14,754 --> 00:23:16,654
Chiang Wei-Shui passed away
at a young age

461
00:23:16,889 --> 00:23:19,085
and the Taiwanese mourned
his death.

462
00:23:19,392 --> 00:23:20,416
On the day of the funeral,

463
00:23:20,660 --> 00:23:23,391
more than 5000 people
showed up to pay tribute.

464
00:23:23,629 --> 00:23:26,758
The procession stretched
for several kilometers.

465
00:23:26,999 --> 00:23:27,966
His passing seemed

466
00:23:28,201 --> 00:23:28,895
to forecast the end of

467
00:23:29,135 --> 00:23:32,503
the era of enlightenment
and awakening.

468
00:23:59,332 --> 00:24:00,766
In the 1920s, the Han Chinese

469
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:01,899
under the Japanese rule
demanded rights of

470
00:24:02,134 --> 00:24:04,796
political participation
with social movements.

471
00:24:05,137 --> 00:24:06,832
But the aborigines
living in the mountains

472
00:24:07,106 --> 00:24:08,073
still lived an oppressed life

473
00:24:08,241 --> 00:24:10,141
under the government's policy
of managing

474
00:24:10,376 --> 00:24:11,969
the aborigines with kindness
and severity.

475
00:24:12,345 --> 00:24:13,710
The Japanese police, in particular,

476
00:24:13,946 --> 00:24:16,745
tyrannized over the aborigines
in every way.

477
00:24:28,661 --> 00:24:29,822
The resentment and hatred

478
00:24:30,129 --> 00:24:31,893
that accumulated over the years

479
00:24:32,131 --> 00:24:33,690
finally caused the Wushe Incident
in 1930

480
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:36,595
which shocked the world.

481
00:24:45,378 --> 00:24:46,903
On the morning of October 27,

482
00:24:47,146 --> 00:24:49,046
Mona Rudao, the chief of Mahebo,

483
00:24:49,248 --> 00:24:51,876
led the Seedeq tribe to
carry out a surprise attack.

484
00:24:52,251 --> 00:24:54,117
A sports meeting was taking place

485
00:24:54,353 --> 00:24:56,185
on the playing field
of Wushe Elementary School.

486
00:24:56,422 --> 00:24:57,753
During the flag raising ceremony,

487
00:24:57,990 --> 00:24:59,822
the Seedeq people in ambush

488
00:25:00,126 --> 00:25:01,184
rushed out at once to attack

489
00:25:01,427 --> 00:25:03,521
the Japanese who were present.

490
00:25:10,970 --> 00:25:11,937
On this battle,

491
00:25:12,171 --> 00:25:14,833
132 Japanese were killed,

492
00:25:15,141 --> 00:25:17,132
215 were wounded,

493
00:25:17,376 --> 00:25:19,777
and two Taiwanese died.

494
00:25:36,062 --> 00:25:37,427
When the Office of
Taiwan Governor-General got news,

495
00:25:37,663 --> 00:25:40,598
they deployed soldiers
and policemen to Wushe.

496
00:25:41,334 --> 00:25:44,326
Seedeq warriors were forced
to hide in caves.

497
00:25:44,837 --> 00:25:47,169
The Japanese then used air raids

498
00:25:47,406 --> 00:25:48,373
and handbills to persuade
them to surrender,

499
00:25:48,607 --> 00:25:49,938
but to no avail.

500
00:25:50,409 --> 00:25:53,037
In the end, blister gas bombs,

501
00:25:53,245 --> 00:25:54,872
banned by the International
Law, were dropped,

502
00:25:55,114 --> 00:25:58,140
resulting in the painful deaths
of a mass of Seedeq people.

503
00:26:12,164 --> 00:26:14,132
This incident shocked people
on the island.

504
00:26:14,367 --> 00:26:17,200
Up until December 8th
when the suppression ceased,

505
00:26:17,470 --> 00:26:20,496
a total of 644 Seedeqs died.

506
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:22,071
The Office of
Taiwan Governor-General

507
00:26:22,274 --> 00:26:24,242
mobilized 1563 soldiers,

508
00:26:24,577 --> 00:26:27,069
1231 policemen,

509
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:29,974
and 1381 non-combatants.

510
00:26:41,260 --> 00:26:43,627
Next we have
Taiwanese singer Chun-Chun

511
00:26:43,863 --> 00:26:47,026
performing "Dance Age."

512
00:27:13,125 --> 00:27:14,650
In the 1920s,

513
00:27:14,894 --> 00:27:17,488
after 20 -odd years
of Japanese occupation,

514
00:27:17,730 --> 00:27:19,095
Taiwan gradually became

515
00:27:19,331 --> 00:27:20,856
a modernized society.

516
00:27:21,434 --> 00:27:23,664
Young men and women who had
received Japanese education

517
00:27:23,903 --> 00:27:25,769
began to break away
from the bonds of tradition

518
00:27:26,005 --> 00:27:28,406
and yearned for an independent life.

519
00:27:28,641 --> 00:27:29,870
Women in particular

520
00:27:30,109 --> 00:27:30,667
finally had a chance

521
00:27:30,910 --> 00:27:33,072
to lead a career life.

522
00:27:34,046 --> 00:27:35,343
Every fashionable man and woman
at the time

523
00:27:35,581 --> 00:27:37,174
were familiar with the slogan

524
00:27:37,917 --> 00:27:40,648
"New world, free love."

525
00:27:52,631 --> 00:27:54,030
In October of 1935,

526
00:27:54,233 --> 00:27:55,064
the Office of Taiwan
Governor-General in the name

527
00:27:55,301 --> 00:27:57,235
of the 40th anniversary of
the Japanese rule,

528
00:27:57,470 --> 00:27:58,835
spent a million dollars

529
00:27:59,071 --> 00:28:01,631
on mobilizing more than
10,000 Taiwanese

530
00:28:01,874 --> 00:28:04,343
to organize an exhibition.

531
00:28:05,077 --> 00:28:06,875
At this exposition

532
00:28:07,113 --> 00:28:08,512
the Office of Governor-General
well publicized

533
00:28:08,747 --> 00:28:11,045
the promises of a modernized
Taiwan.

534
00:28:11,283 --> 00:28:12,773
It also used this opportunity

535
00:28:13,085 --> 00:28:15,520
to flaunt domestically
and internationally

536
00:28:15,754 --> 00:28:18,052
their accomplishments in Taiwan.

537
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:30,592
As people's spending power
increases,

538
00:28:30,836 --> 00:28:33,271
and ideas of sports and
recreation emerge,

539
00:28:33,506 --> 00:28:34,996
there was a surge of parks,
western-styled restaurants,

540
00:28:35,207 --> 00:28:38,404
department stores and movie theaters.

541
00:28:38,911 --> 00:28:41,039
The modernization of the
lives of the common people

542
00:28:41,280 --> 00:28:42,839
brought out the lively side

543
00:28:43,082 --> 00:28:45,050
of Taiwanese society.

544
00:29:13,379 --> 00:29:16,280
In order to strengthen
the national defense,

545
00:29:16,515 --> 00:29:21,885
we must ensure the empire's
position in East Asia

546
00:29:22,121 --> 00:29:26,388
and expand into the South Seas.

547
00:29:29,094 --> 00:29:30,858
In the early 1930s,

548
00:29:31,096 --> 00:29:33,064
Japanese militarism came to power.

549
00:29:33,299 --> 00:29:34,027
They transformed the existing

550
00:29:34,266 --> 00:29:36,132
economic policy of

551
00:29:36,368 --> 00:29:37,130
agricultural Taiwan into

552
00:29:37,369 --> 00:29:39,599
"Agricultural Southeast Asia,
Industrial Taiwan.”

553
00:29:40,472 --> 00:29:42,201
Then in 1936,

554
00:29:42,474 --> 00:29:43,441
the Go-South Policy
officially became

555
00:29:43,676 --> 00:29:46,111
the national policy
of the Japanese Empire.

556
00:29:46,712 --> 00:29:50,012
Taiwan became the springboard
to the South.

557
00:29:51,050 --> 00:29:52,711
In order to meet armament needs,

558
00:29:53,085 --> 00:29:56,020
metal, mechanical,
shipbuilding, cement,

559
00:29:56,188 --> 00:29:58,179
and chemical industries in Taiwan

560
00:29:58,424 --> 00:30:00,188
developed at a rapid pace.

561
00:30:00,859 --> 00:30:02,224
The industrialization

562
00:30:02,461 --> 00:30:04,486
led to the rapid growth
in Taiwanese economy.

563
00:30:04,964 --> 00:30:07,023
In the late 1930s,

564
00:30:07,233 --> 00:30:08,428
the per capita income in Taiwan

565
00:30:08,667 --> 00:30:10,863
was 50% more than that in Korea.

566
00:30:11,437 --> 00:30:12,336
Taiwan was becoming

567
00:30:12,571 --> 00:30:14,539
an industrialized society.

568
00:30:44,737 --> 00:30:48,002
The Marco Polo Bridge Incident
of 1937

569
00:30:48,274 --> 00:30:49,366
ignited the war between
China and Japan

570
00:30:49,608 --> 00:30:51,542
that would last for eight years.

571
00:30:52,177 --> 00:30:53,076
In order to have
the Taiwanese people

572
00:30:53,312 --> 00:30:55,872
wholeheartedly on Japan's side,

573
00:30:56,382 --> 00:30:57,440
the Office of
Taiwan Governor-General

574
00:30:57,683 --> 00:31:00,015
aggressively launched
the Kominka Movement

575
00:31:00,452 --> 00:31:02,250
to thoroughly transform

576
00:31:02,488 --> 00:31:03,853
the Taiwanese into Japanese.

577
00:31:09,194 --> 00:31:11,253
During the Kominka Movement,
the Japanese also set up

578
00:31:11,497 --> 00:31:14,728
the Main Hall Improvement
Movement,

579
00:31:15,167 --> 00:31:16,293
which forced Taiwanese people

580
00:31:16,535 --> 00:31:19,129
to replace the deities
they originally worshipped

581
00:31:19,371 --> 00:31:21,430
with the Shinto goddess

582
00:31:21,674 --> 00:31:23,199
Amaterasu.

583
00:31:24,576 --> 00:31:25,907
Is this right to put the goddess
in this way?

584
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:03,774
The colonizers believed that

585
00:32:04,016 --> 00:32:05,415
speaking Japanese was imperative

586
00:32:05,651 --> 00:32:07,176
in becoming a real Japanese.

587
00:32:07,419 --> 00:32:07,908
So campaigns to make Japanese

588
00:32:08,153 --> 00:32:10,485
the national language

589
00:32:10,723 --> 00:32:12,555
spread like wildfire.

590
00:32:13,392 --> 00:32:14,757
They also encouraged the Taiwanese

591
00:32:14,993 --> 00:32:16,518
to use Japanese names.

592
00:32:24,336 --> 00:32:28,830
I am Kobayashi Sajio.

593
00:32:29,608 --> 00:32:30,507
A-Ho.

594
00:32:43,122 --> 00:32:44,749
When the Second Sino-Japanese
War broke out,

595
00:32:44,990 --> 00:32:46,924
Taiwanese men didn't get drafted,

596
00:32:47,159 --> 00:32:49,856
but they went to China

597
00:32:50,095 --> 00:32:51,324
as non-combatants
and military farmers,

598
00:32:51,563 --> 00:32:54,157
singing military songs

599
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:56,300
adapted from Taiwanese songs.

600
00:32:59,304 --> 00:33:00,635
Hurry up.

601
00:33:01,273 --> 00:33:02,900
Dig those trenches.

602
00:33:03,142 --> 00:33:03,768
Yes, sir.

603
00:33:04,009 --> 00:33:05,875
This will increase our combat force.

604
00:33:06,111 --> 00:33:06,771
Yes, sir.

605
00:33:07,012 --> 00:33:08,707
Hurry up.

606
00:33:28,467 --> 00:33:30,094
Japan thought that the battle in China

607
00:33:30,335 --> 00:33:32,736
would end soon.

608
00:33:33,138 --> 00:33:36,108
They didn't expect
to get caught up in it.

609
00:33:36,842 --> 00:33:39,368
In order to break through
the stalemate,

610
00:33:39,611 --> 00:33:41,705
Japan decided to wage wars
in Southeast Asia

611
00:33:41,947 --> 00:33:43,938
and in areas around
the Pacific Ocean,

612
00:33:44,249 --> 00:33:46,911
which resulted in the Pacific War.

613
00:33:50,622 --> 00:33:52,386
With the expansion of the battlefield,

614
00:33:52,624 --> 00:33:54,058
the Japanese changed their policy

615
00:33:54,226 --> 00:33:56,422
of not recruiting

616
00:33:56,662 --> 00:33:57,857
Taiwanese soldiers.

617
00:33:58,263 --> 00:33:59,856
In 1942,

618
00:34:00,165 --> 00:34:01,894
the Office of Taiwan
Governor-General implemented

619
00:34:02,134 --> 00:34:03,829
the Special Volunteer Policy,

620
00:34:04,102 --> 00:34:06,901
which brought
an upsurge of volunteers.

621
00:34:10,476 --> 00:34:12,467
They set up street stands
for people to sign up.

622
00:34:13,512 --> 00:34:14,673
When a young man walks by,

623
00:34:15,113 --> 00:34:16,706
a Japanese officer
would hold him down and say,

624
00:34:17,216 --> 00:34:19,446
"You have a great physique.

625
00:34:20,018 --> 00:34:21,747
Are you willing to sacrifice
for the state?”

626
00:34:22,654 --> 00:34:23,883
Under the circumstance,

627
00:34:24,122 --> 00:34:25,089
one could do nothing but sign up.

628
00:34:25,290 --> 00:34:27,554
No one dares to refuse.

629
00:34:39,905 --> 00:34:42,067
Most of the volunteers

630
00:34:42,307 --> 00:34:44,833
were sent to Southeast Asia

631
00:34:45,077 --> 00:34:46,442
to fight the Americans.

632
00:34:46,912 --> 00:34:47,606
In this year,

633
00:34:47,846 --> 00:34:49,871
the Japanese were beginning

634
00:34:50,115 --> 00:34:51,583
to lose their stand
in the Pacific battlefields.

635
00:35:29,121 --> 00:35:30,680
The Japanese Army also
enlisted Taiwanese aborigines

636
00:35:30,923 --> 00:35:32,982
to form the Takaza Volunteers,

637
00:35:33,325 --> 00:35:35,020
who carried out
the most dangerous mission

638
00:35:35,260 --> 00:35:37,319
to fight at the battle front.

639
00:35:38,063 --> 00:35:39,861
Not only the men,

640
00:35:40,098 --> 00:35:40,826
but also Taiwanese women

641
00:35:41,066 --> 00:35:43,865
were mobilized to serve as nurses.

642
00:35:44,436 --> 00:35:46,734
The Japanese military
rounded up comfort women

643
00:35:46,972 --> 00:35:47,666
from various occupied
and colonized territories

644
00:35:47,906 --> 00:35:50,170
to serve Japanese soldiers
in the war zones.

645
00:35:50,542 --> 00:35:53,034
Taiwanese women were
no exceptions.

646
00:36:14,967 --> 00:36:17,595
“Brave warriors of the front,

647
00:36:17,836 --> 00:36:19,736
ever since the holy battle
of Greater East Asia started,

648
00:36:19,972 --> 00:36:21,838
wherever you have been,

649
00:36:22,107 --> 00:36:23,472
you win all the battles.

650
00:36:23,976 --> 00:36:27,469
We have occupied
innumerable territories.

651
00:36:27,713 --> 00:36:28,805
This is all thanks

652
00:36:29,114 --> 00:36:30,843
to your hard work

653
00:36:31,116 --> 00:36:33,608
which is beyond description.”

654
00:36:34,786 --> 00:36:36,015
In April of 1941,

655
00:36:36,188 --> 00:36:38,213
right before the start of
the Pacific War,

656
00:36:38,457 --> 00:36:40,824
the Public Service Association of
Imperial Subjects was set up.

657
00:36:41,460 --> 00:36:44,293
Various secondary groups emerged

658
00:36:44,529 --> 00:36:47,624
under its aggressive mobilization.

659
00:36:47,866 --> 00:36:49,129
Even public school students

660
00:36:49,368 --> 00:36:51,427
were called upon to write letters.

661
00:36:56,241 --> 00:36:57,436
“We at the home front,

662
00:36:57,676 --> 00:36:59,110
like you warriors,

663
00:36:59,344 --> 00:37:01,210
are busy with our missions

664
00:37:01,446 --> 00:37:05,405
and with air-raid drill.

665
00:37:05,651 --> 00:37:09,087
The youth leagues, too,
are hard at work.”

666
00:37:19,665 --> 00:37:22,066
“Going to the Shinto shrine
to pray

667
00:37:22,267 --> 00:37:24,429
that you may win in battles

668
00:37:24,670 --> 00:37:27,071
has become our daily homework.”

669
00:37:28,740 --> 00:37:31,937
“We will defend the home front.
Do not worry.

670
00:37:32,177 --> 00:37:35,875
Strive to defeat the British
and the Americans.

671
00:37:36,648 --> 00:37:39,140
Under the Greater East Asia
Co-Prosperity Sphere,

672
00:37:39,384 --> 00:37:42,046
the day of justice and glory
is approaching.

673
00:37:42,287 --> 00:37:45,018
We will pray for you...”

674
00:37:45,257 --> 00:37:48,022
The Battle of Midway
in June of 1942

675
00:37:48,193 --> 00:37:50,059
saw Japan's first defeat.

676
00:37:50,328 --> 00:37:53,025
The U.S. took the offensive
while Japan became defensive.

677
00:37:53,732 --> 00:37:57,191
In 1943, the U.S.
began counterattacking

678
00:37:57,569 --> 00:37:59,594
as the Japanese continued to retreat.

679
00:38:00,138 --> 00:38:02,038
The battle made a U-turn.

680
00:38:04,943 --> 00:38:07,037
Due to heavy loss of troops,

681
00:38:07,312 --> 00:38:09,872
Japan began to draft students
into the war.

682
00:38:10,115 --> 00:38:11,514
Taiwan was no exception.

683
00:38:14,653 --> 00:38:16,644
More than 10,000 students

684
00:38:16,888 --> 00:38:18,185
ranging from ages 12 to 19

685
00:38:18,423 --> 00:38:20,118
were called to Japan

686
00:38:20,425 --> 00:38:21,688
by the Japanese Navy

687
00:38:21,927 --> 00:38:24,794
to work in military factories

688
00:38:25,097 --> 00:38:27,429
where they were busy with
arms production,

689
00:38:27,666 --> 00:38:29,760
such as airplanes, torpedoes,
and missiles.

690
00:39:04,102 --> 00:39:07,037
As the war extended
and situations worsened

691
00:39:07,239 --> 00:39:09,037
regulations such as

692
00:39:09,241 --> 00:39:11,608
consumption and goods controls,

693
00:39:11,843 --> 00:39:13,937
and food rationings
were implemented,

694
00:39:14,179 --> 00:39:17,114
which affected
the lives of the Taiwanese.

695
00:39:32,264 --> 00:39:33,698
So small?

696
00:39:36,268 --> 00:39:37,861
Don't you have anything else?

697
00:39:40,906 --> 00:39:42,897
We're using this money
to buy planes.

698
00:40:12,337 --> 00:40:16,433
If a leg wound gets infected,

699
00:40:17,075 --> 00:40:18,702
it never gets better.

700
00:40:19,511 --> 00:40:21,309
Everyday tons of patients

701
00:40:21,546 --> 00:40:23,139
wait in line to be treated.

702
00:40:23,381 --> 00:40:26,749
Lifting the trouser leg,
you see a lot of maggots.

703
00:40:26,985 --> 00:40:28,646
It's very scary.

704
00:40:29,321 --> 00:40:30,516
In 1944,

705
00:40:30,755 --> 00:40:32,416
Taiwan, originally being

706
00:40:32,657 --> 00:40:35,388
a liaison stronghold

707
00:40:35,694 --> 00:40:36,456
for the Southeast Asian
battlefields,

708
00:40:36,695 --> 00:40:39,460
became the front line
of the Japanese defense.

709
00:40:40,332 --> 00:40:42,801
On September 1st, the Office
of Taiwan Governor-General

710
00:40:43,034 --> 00:40:45,025
announced the implementation
of a draft system in Taiwan.

711
00:40:45,470 --> 00:40:47,268
More than 80,000 Taiwanese

712
00:40:47,505 --> 00:40:50,770
fought for Japan
in the Pacific War.

713
00:40:51,309 --> 00:40:54,176
And more than 120,000
were enlisted

714
00:40:54,412 --> 00:40:56,380
as civilian employees
and non-combatants.

715
00:41:38,290 --> 00:41:40,486
Chen Chien-Wu, a poet,

716
00:41:40,725 --> 00:41:43,854
was a young volunteer
from Taiwan.

717
00:41:44,329 --> 00:41:46,161
In "Pigeon,"

718
00:41:46,398 --> 00:41:48,389
he expressed a deep mourning

719
00:41:48,633 --> 00:41:50,658
for the Taiwanese soldiers
who died in the war.

720
00:43:11,683 --> 00:43:13,879
This Greater East Asia
crusade

721
00:43:14,119 --> 00:43:14,881
took the lives of

722
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:17,953
more than 30,000 Taiwanese.

723
00:43:18,456 --> 00:43:19,582
After the Second World War,

724
00:43:19,824 --> 00:43:21,918
the KMT took over Taiwan.

725
00:43:22,160 --> 00:43:24,720
What was once an enemy state

726
00:43:24,963 --> 00:43:26,362
became the fatherland to the
Taiwanese Japanese soldiers

727
00:43:26,631 --> 00:43:28,531
who thus became confused.

728
00:43:28,933 --> 00:43:30,560
Who am I fighting for?

729
00:43:30,802 --> 00:43:31,997
What am I fighting for?

730
00:43:32,337 --> 00:43:33,566
Did we lose

731
00:43:33,805 --> 00:43:34,863
or did we win?

732
00:43:35,640 --> 00:43:37,836
Even years after the war,

733
00:43:38,076 --> 00:43:40,807
these questions still

734
00:43:41,079 --> 00:43:42,308
surfaced in their nightmares

735
00:43:42,547 --> 00:43:43,912
and would never go away.

736
00:43:52,424 --> 00:43:58,887
Defense-in-depth paired with
guerilla warfare...

737
00:43:59,130 --> 00:44:00,620
At the end of 1943,

738
00:44:00,865 --> 00:44:02,162
The Allies began to
take the offensive

739
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:04,425
on the Pacific battlefield.

740
00:44:05,103 --> 00:44:07,629
Taiwan became the landing
target for the Americans.

741
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:11,639
The Office of Taiwan Governor-General
prepared for war in Taiwan.

742
00:44:11,976 --> 00:44:13,774
They planned to fight until the last

743
00:44:14,012 --> 00:44:15,173
moment when every one was
killed and all arms were

744
00:44:15,547 --> 00:44:18,175
used up to protect the safety
of Japan proper.

745
00:44:39,737 --> 00:44:41,501
In the autumn of 1944,

746
00:44:41,739 --> 00:44:42,570
Taiwan began to suffer

747
00:44:42,807 --> 00:44:45,469
heavy bombardments from the U.S.

748
00:44:45,743 --> 00:44:48,576
All manufacturing sectors
nearly came to a stop,

749
00:44:48,847 --> 00:44:51,714
so did industrial developments.

750
00:44:51,950 --> 00:44:53,281
People were evacuated

751
00:44:53,518 --> 00:44:55,316
from cities to the countryside.

752
00:44:56,187 --> 00:44:58,087
When the air-raid alarm sounded,

753
00:44:58,323 --> 00:45:00,382
people hid in air-raid shelters,

754
00:45:00,625 --> 00:45:02,286
woods or caves.

755
00:45:02,794 --> 00:45:05,923
Not only were they worried about

756
00:45:06,164 --> 00:45:07,188
their homes being destroyed,

757
00:45:07,432 --> 00:45:09,400
but also uncertain about the future.

758
00:45:10,602 --> 00:45:12,502
As the days passed,

759
00:45:12,770 --> 00:45:15,865
the Taiwanese prayed for
the war to end.

760
00:45:24,482 --> 00:45:27,213
Taiwanese intellectuals in
the mid-Japanese Occupation

761
00:45:27,452 --> 00:45:28,886
Era criticized and reflected

762
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:31,316
on the nature of the Taiwanese.

763
00:45:31,856 --> 00:45:34,188
In contrast to
the Japanese ruling class,

764
00:45:34,425 --> 00:45:35,654
the people of Taiwan

765
00:45:35,894 --> 00:45:38,192
began to call themselves Taiwanese.

766
00:45:39,063 --> 00:45:40,861
In the history of Taiwan,

767
00:45:41,099 --> 00:45:41,895
This was the earliest appearance

768
00:45:42,133 --> 00:45:44,227
of Taiwanese consciousness.

769
00:45:47,939 --> 00:45:50,670
Just when this consciousness

770
00:45:50,909 --> 00:45:52,468
began to sprout,

771
00:45:52,911 --> 00:45:54,936
World War II broke out.

772
00:45:55,180 --> 00:45:57,478
The Japanese government
accelerated

773
00:45:57,715 --> 00:45:59,342
the Kominka policy in Taiwan,

774
00:45:59,584 --> 00:46:02,178
hoping to transform
Taiwanese into Japanese.

775
00:46:29,414 --> 00:46:31,940
After years of war,

776
00:46:32,183 --> 00:46:34,845
Japan finally surrendered

777
00:46:35,086 --> 00:46:36,918
unconditionally on August 15, 1945,

778
00:46:37,155 --> 00:46:38,714
and the Taiwanese were freed.

779
00:46:39,057 --> 00:46:41,025
The Taiwanese consciousness
resurfaced

780
00:46:41,459 --> 00:46:44,429
and the claims and pursuits
of the Taiwanese were voiced.

781
00:46:44,662 --> 00:46:46,221
This became the main force
influencing

782
00:46:46,464 --> 00:46:49,229
the development of Taiwan
after the Second World War.

